Package com.intland.codebeamer.persistence.dto.base

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BaseDto
    All DTO classes must extend this marker interface.
    CrudContainedReferableDto
    All entity classes that support CRUD operations for contained (child) entities should implement this.
    CrudReferableDto
    All entity classes that support CRUD operations should implement this.
    EntityPermission<T extends NamedDto & ReferableDto>
    The basic interface of an entity permission
    ProjectAwareDto
    All DTO classes with project property must implement this.
    ReadOnlyDto
    A marker interface to identify read-only Dtos, that don't allow to change their attributes.
    ReferableDto
    All DTO classes that can be linked through URLs and interwiki references should implement this.
    ReferenceAccessor<T extends ReferenceDto,H>
    The generic interface of a Reference Accessor that allows to resolve references of type T from objects of type H that are not instances of @{link ReferenceHolderDto}
    ReferenceHolderDto<T extends ReferenceDto>
    The interface of a Dto that holds a reference to another object.
    RemovableDto
    All DTO classes that support the remove operation must implement this.
    VersionedReferableDto
    All DTO classes that are both ReferableDto and versioned should implement this.
    WriteControlledDto
    All DTO classes with a boolean writable flag must implement this.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCommentDto
    Each comment DTO must extend this.
    AbstractReferenceDto<F extends ReferenceDto,T extends ReferenceDto>
    Each DTO that constitutes a link/association between two entities in the system or between one entity and an external URL, must extend this class.
    AbstractReferenceDto.AltKey<F extends ReferenceDto,T extends ReferenceDto>
    A special Predicate to find/compare AbstractReferenceDtos by alternate key {fromTypeId, fromId, toTypeId, toId, url}
    DescribeableDto
    All named DTO classes with description property must extend this.
    DescribeableDto.DescriptionComparator
    A special Comparator to compare/sort DescribeableDto by description
    IdentifiableDto
    All DTO classes with id property must extend this.
    IdentifiableDto.IdComparator
    A special Comparator implementation to compare two IdentifiableDtos by id
    IdentifiableFieldValueDto
    This class represents a field value of an IdentifiableDto.
    IdentifiablePropertyValueDto
    A simple holder for a named property value of an IdentifiableDto
    LinkedReferenceFilterDto
    A special read-only ReferenceFilterDto that is linked to a template reference filter.
    NamedDto
    All DTO classes with name property must extend this.
    NamedDto.NameComparator
    A special Comparator implementation to compare two NamedDtos by name
    ObjectCommentDto<T extends ReferenceDto>
    A comment plus a reference to the comment owner
    ReadOnlyNamedDto
    A special NamedDto that doesn't allow to change it's attributes All attempts to invoke a property setter method will throw an UnsupportedOperationException
    ReadOnlyReferenceDto<T extends ReferableDto>
    A special ReferenceDto that doesn't allow to change it's attributes All attempts to invoke a property setter method will throw an UnsupportedOperationException
    ReadOnlyReferenceFilterDto
    A special ReferenceFilterDto that doesn't allow to change it's attributes All attempts to invoke a property setter method will throw an UnsupportedOperationException
    ReferableDto.DescriptionComparator
    A special Comparator implementation to compare two ReferableDtos by short description
    ReferenceDto<T extends ReferableDto>
    A ReferenceDto represents a reference to a ReferableDto.
    ReferenceFilterDto
    A named filter for referenced objects of a specific type in a specific domain
    ReleaseId
    A CodeBeamer release number contains of a sequence of major to minor release numbers, separated by '.'.
    VersionReferenceDto<T extends ReferableDto>
    A special reference to a specific version of the referenced object
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    LicenseKind  
    Position
    A simple Enumeration to define a position of an object relative to another object in a tree
    UserLicenseType
    The available combinations of UserType and LicenseKind
    UserType
    The fixed enumeration of different user types regarding licensing
